					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3166727#post-3654949</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3166727/scp-3560#post-3654949</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 19 Dec 2017 01:23:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>The sort of stuff I would be curious about in an article like this would be field research into the degree to which you can destroy these things. If you put the robot in an extremely strong acid, how much would it dissolve as compared to a non-ghost robot? Or similar experiments, acid might generally be ineffective. If these portal things pop up out of nowhere, perhaps it could be justified.</p> </blockquote> <p>So, these robo-ghosts are basically indestructible while inside their little pocket dimension, and are basically apparitions outside the pocket dimension, which renders them immune to traditional small arms and other weapons. In fact at the end of the article, the Foundation has manufactured a device called Hoffman Portable Electro-Thaumic Units (based off this article <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/grant-request-for-utilization-of-electro-thaumic-computers-t">here</a>) that have proven quite effective in exorcising the robo-ghosts and keeping them in their little dimension.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3166727#post-3654742</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3166727/scp-3560#post-3654742</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 18 Dec 2017 17:55:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Spinachguy</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2084624</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Ah, cool. Robot ghosts are always fun, I was wondering if i'd ever see any. Reminds me of some stuff I had thought up a long time ago, maybe I could take a look at working it into an SCP.</p> <p>The sort of stuff I would be curious about in an article like this would be field research into the degree to which you can destroy these things. If you put the robot in an extremely strong acid, how much would it dissolve as compared to a non-ghost robot? Or similar experiments, acid might generally be ineffective. If these portal things pop up out of nowhere, perhaps it could be justified.</p> <p>As for saving the MTF squad surrounded by zombie robots, it would take the work of a tactical geniu-<br /> *ahem*<br /> &#8230;something in my throat. Sorry.</p> <p>Anyway, good spooky robot article! +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
