					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3166727#post-3558403</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3166727/scp-3560#post-3558403</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 26 Jul 2017 15:35:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>bittermixin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3085453</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The primary anomaly actually reminds me somewhat of Series 1.</p> <p>Beyond that, it's a very well-constructed article with a very consistent clinical tone- the dialogue is very realistic, I especially enjoyed the interview. Though part of me still feels as if its lacking something. When you present a concept as interesting as 'portal to a pissed-off robot graveyard', it really needs to go above and beyond to meet expectations- and for me, it was good, it just didn't really blow me away. Perhaps it just isn't my sort of article.</p> <p>Novote for now.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
